## Business Problem

Building something that works is not the same as building something that is reliable, secure, cost-efficient, and operationally sound. The AWS Well-Architected Framework gives architects and account managers a structured way to evaluate any workload against proven best practices — and identify the highest-priority improvements.

This project applies the Well-Architected Framework to the URL shortener built in Project 1, producing a formal review report exactly as an SA would deliver to a customer.

---

## Workload Reviewed

**Project 1 — Serverless URL Shortener**  
Services: API Gateway, Lambda, DynamoDB, IAM, CloudWatch

---

## The 6 Pillars

| Pillar | What it evaluates |
|--------|------------------|
| Operational Excellence | How well can you run, monitor, and improve the workload? |
| Security | How well are you protecting data, systems, and assets? |
| Reliability | Can the workload recover from failures and meet demand? |
| Performance Efficiency | Are you using resources efficiently as requirements change? |
| Cost Optimization | Are you avoiding unnecessary costs? |
| Sustainability | Are you minimizing environmental impact? |

